      • betweenSameTimeout

        public NumericProperty betweenSameTimeout
        betweenSameTimeout When in Continuous triggering mode, this parameter sets the minimum time that must elapse before the scan engine decodes a second bar code identical to one just decoded. This reduces the risk of accidently scanning the same symbol twice. It is programmable in 0.1 second increments from 0.0 to 9.9 seconds.If the value exceeds the range, the value is set at full scale.From 0 to 99.

      • decodeTimeout

        public NumericProperty decodeTimeout
        decodeTimeoutThis scanner engin sets the maximum time decode processing continues during a scan attempt. It is programmable in 0.1 second increments from 0.50 to 10 seconds.5 to 99 = 0.5 to 10 seconds. If the value exceeds the range, the value is set at full scale.

      • linerSecurityLevel

        public NumericProperty linerSecurityLevel
        linerSecurityLevelThe parameter offers four levels(1 to 4.) of decode security for linear code types (e.g. Code 39, Interleaved 2 of 5). Select higher security levels for decreasing levels of bar code quality. As security levels increase, the scan engine’s aggressiveness decreases.

      • image_inverse_1d

        public NumericProperty image_inverse_1d
        Set the 1D inverse decoder setting:
        • *0 - Regular Only - the decoder decodes regular 1D bar codes only.
        • 1 - Inverse Only - the decoder decodes inverse 1D bar codes only.
        • 2 - Inverse Autodetect - the decoder decodes both regular and inverse 1D bar codes.

      • image_coding_format

        public NumericProperty image_coding_format
        Set the 2D Chinese character coding format setting:
        • *0 - utf-8 coding format.
        • 1 - gb2312 coding format.
